<!DOCTYPE html>
<h1 id="name">Chadly D. Hortin</h1>
<h3 id="title">SVP, Client Experience</h3>
<div id="bio">
	<h3>SVP, Client Experience</h3>
	<div id="preview">
		<p>Chadly Hortin has more than 20 years of senior-level executive experience in technology design, consumer behavior analysis, product development, and market creation.</p>
		<p>He works directly with Mindshare&rsquo;s clients and client advisors to establish strong relationships and maximize the value of each client&rsquo;s customer reviews.</p>
	</div>
	<p>Chadly assists companies in applying technology at the point of customer interaction to enhance the quality of each customer experience. He has implemented and supported solutions with many Fortune 500 companies, and he has taught courses and provided corporate training for hundreds of organizations.</p>
	<p>Chadly presents at industry and company conferences on measuring and improving customer and employee satisfaction. He has built a team of client advisors who work with clients to collect quality customer and employee feedback, interpret and provide insights from the data, and provide guidance in making operational improvements.</p>
	<p>As senior vice president of client experience at Mindshare Technologies, Chadly works with a broad base of clients, providing training on customer feedback programs, consulting on customer experience improvement initiatives, and presenting findings from customer data for over 1,000 business organizations.</p>
	<p>As vice president at Sterling Wentworth Corporation from 1985 to 1999, and then SunGard Data Systems from 1999 to 2006, Chadly built experience in the design, deployment, and training of complex expert system technologies in small and large organizations.</p>
	<p>At Mindshare Technologies, Chadly focuses on interpreting data, uncovering key insights, and identifying customer-driven actions to improve our clients&rsquo; businesses. He works to leverage customer reviews to increase business intelligence and add measurable value to each client&rsquo;s business.</p>
	<p>Chadly loves to create and share memorable outdoor experiences with his family and friends. He uses these experiences as an opportunity to practice the principles that drive success in all endeavors: be genuine, be passionate, be relevant, and be prepared. </p>
	<p>Chadly has a B.S. in accounting from the University of Utah as well as an MBA and law degree from Brigham Young University.</p>
</div>